# Git Worktree Workflow

Always work in a git worktree, never in the main working directory.

- Create worktree: `git worktree add <path> <branch>`
- On completion: sync .sisyphus state back, merge worktree branch into main, remove worktree
- Commit after each logical change using conventional commits
- Push when user confirms work is complete
- Before finishing: verify CI/github actions passes, fix if red
- When user approves push to main: merge branch, delete remote branch, remove worktree
